    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-02-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-02-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="567"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d567">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/4621</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chief of the Division of Near Eastern Affairs</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Chargé at Tangier</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Childs</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-02-17">February 17,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Rives</hi>: Paraphrases of your telegrams no. 4 of
                    January 5 and no. 10 of January 7, 1942, were transmitted to the Secretary of
                    War under cover of a communication from the Department, in which the views of
                    the War Department were requested in order that appropriate study might be given
                    to the matter under review.</p>
                <p>The Secretary of War has replied to the effect that it is felt that all possible
                    means and every occasion should be taken to cultivate the friendship and good
                    will of the person to whom reference was made in your telegrams. It was added
                    that any contacts which may create a basis of <hi rend="italic"
                        >rapprochement</hi> between the Spanish civil and military authorities and
                    ourselves that might be of value and aid in a military way in the future should
                    be furthered at this time.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wallace Murray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
